    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-10-28T19:37:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-10-28T19:37:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.2553/10–2854: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 502<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Iran</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d502fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_SJH1"
                            >Stutesman</persName> and approved by Under Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> after being cleared with Ambassador
                            <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">Henderson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-10-28T19:37:00-05:00"
                            >October 28, 1954—7:37 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>843. Personal from <persName corresp="#p_HHJ1">Hoover</persName> to Foreign
                    Minister. The news that the Iranian Parliament has today ratified the oil
                        agreement<note n="2" xml:id="d502fn2">
                        <p>On Oct. 28 the Embassy in Tehran informed the Department that the Iranian
                            Senate had passed the oil bill that day, with 41 votes in favor, 4
                            against, and 3 abstentions. (Telegram 962; 888.2553/10–2854)</p>
                        <p>The Department issued a press release, dated Oct. 28, announcing that on
                            Oct. 28 the agreement in principle, signed on Aug. 5, between the
                            Government of Iran and the International Oil Consortium, was ratified by
                            the Iranian Senate. For text, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                                >Bulletin</hi>, Nov. 8, 1954, p. 683.</p>
                    </note> is wonderful news indeed and marks a significant victory by those forces
                    in Iran dedicated to the principle that Iran is to move forward toward social
                    and economic development in friendly cooperation with other nations of the free
                    world.</p>
                <p>Please convey my heartiest congratulations on this significant occasion to His
                    Imperial Majesty, the Prime Minister, Dr. <persName corresp="#p_ADA1"
                        >Amini</persName> and all the others in your government who contributed to
                    the accomplishment of this great achievement which the whole free world
                        admires.<note n="3" xml:id="d502fn3">On Oct. 29 the Embassy in Tehran,
                        informed the Department that the Shah signed the oil bill that day.
                        (Telegram 974; 888.2553/10–2954)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
